---
type Variant = "install" | "changelog" | "reference";

const { variant, published } = Astro.props as {
  variant: Variant;
  published: boolean;
};

const releaseLabel = published
  ? "v0.5.0 · Pre-v1 public alpha"
  : "Target v0.5.0 · Pre-v1 public alpha preview";
---

<section class="release-supplement" aria-labelledby={`release-v050-${variant}`}>
  <p class="release-label">{releaseLabel}</p>

  {variant === "install" && (
    <>
      <h2 id="release-v050-install">Prepare an existing repo for loops</h2>
      <p>
        Preview mdkg-managed scaffold changes before applying them. The upgrade
        path adds the loop scaffold, bundled templates, and loop-execution skill
        while preserving repo-local overlays and canonical MANIFEST naming.
      </p>
      <pre><code>mdkg upgrade
mdkg upgrade --apply
mdkg validate
mdkg loop list</code></pre>
      <p>
        <a href="/loops/">Review the loop model</a> before forking a template.
        Legacy SPEC compatibility remains unchanged for this release.
      </p>
      {!published && (
        <p class="preview-note">
          This is a local release preview. It does not claim that v0.5.0 is
          available from npm.
        </p>
      )}
    </>
  )}

  {variant === "changelog" && (
    <>
      <h2 id="release-v050-changelog">First-class reusable loops</h2>
      <p>
        v0.5.0 adds durable process nodes for audits and planning work that can
        span goals, decisions, evidence lanes, blocker recovery, and attempts.
      </p>
      <h3>Release highlights</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>One first-class <code>loop</code> node type for templates, scoped forks, and run-bearing process state.</li>
        <li>Seven bundled read-only or planning templates, led by the security audit.</li>
        <li>Identity-bound readiness questions, approvals, evidence, and typed waivers.</li>
        <li>Observational fork dry-runs plus goal-like <code>plan</code>, <code>next</code>, and <code>runs</code> inspection.</li>
        <li>Blocker continuation that keeps other authorized lanes moving before the whole loop blocks.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Start with the <a href="/loops/security-audit/">read-only security audit walkthrough</a>.
        mdkg preserves process state; the coding-agent harness executes agents
        and tools.
      </p>
      {!published && (
        <p class="preview-note">
          Draft release facts for local verification only. This preview does not
          claim npm availability; Goal 64 owns final version and changelog
          publication.
        </p>
      )}
    </>
  )}

  {variant === "reference" && (
    <>
      <h2 id="release-v050-reference">Loop command family</h2>
      <p>
        Use raw loop creation for a custom process, or inspect and fork a bundled
        template. The inspection commands do not execute agents or tools.
      </p>
      <pre><code>mdkg new loop "TITLE"
mdkg loop list
mdkg loop show LOOP_OR_TEMPLATE
mdkg loop fork TEMPLATE --scope SCOPE --dry-run
mdkg loop plan LOOP_ID
mdkg loop next LOOP_ID
mdkg loop runs LOOP_ID</code></pre>
      <p>
        Run <code>mdkg loop --help</code> for the installed command contract, or
        read <a href="/loops/templates-and-forks/">Templates and forks</a> for the
        operating model.
      </p>
      {!published && (
        <p class="preview-note">
          This reference supplement is visible only in the local v0.5.0 preview.
        </p>
      )}
    </>
  )}
</section>

<style>
  .release-supplement {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--sl-color-hairline);
  }

  .release-label {
    width: fit-content;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-accent);
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    color: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
    font-family: var(--__sl-font-mono);
    font-size: var(--sl-text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .release-supplement h2,
  .release-supplement h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .release-supplement p,
  .release-supplement ul,
  .release-supplement pre {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .release-supplement pre {
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .preview-note {
    padding-inline-start: 1rem;
    border-inline-start: 3px solid var(--sl-color-orange);
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-2);
  }

  @media (forced-colors: active) {
    .release-label,
    .preview-note {
      border-color: CanvasText;
    }
  }
</style>
